The Health Department has recorded 2 327 new COVID-19 cases, taking the number of total infections to 1 498 766 in the last 24 hours. There have been a further 230 COVID-19 related deaths in the country, bringing the national death toll to 48 708. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Limpopo. “Regrettably, we report 230 more COVID-19 related deaths: 24 from Eastern Cape, 7 from the Free State, 21 from Gauteng, 27 from KwaZulu-Natal, 122 from Limpopo, 10 from Mpumalanga, 0 from North West, 0 from Northern Cape and 19 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative total number of tests conducted to date is 8 807 299. The total number of recoveries stands at 1 403 214. SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 325 623 193 487 61 030 68 401 UNALLOCATED 0 11 165 1 662 1 203 DEATHS 3 032 10 965 9 371 9 373 1 057 650 86163 399 922 59 790 33 211 275 099  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 78 876 18 FEBRUARY 2021 1 498 766 48 708 8 807 299 1 403 214 2 327 230 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));